Hi
 
I was prompted by gddccontrol 0.4.3 to send you the following message:
LANG= LC_ALL= ddccontrol -p -c -d
 
Here's some additional information:
 
Monitor:
Model: Dell P2418HZm
Firmware: M2C101
Connected via: HDMI
 
Working functions:
Setting brightness
Setting contrast
Setting maximum color levels
Restoring default brightness & contrast
Restoring factory default color
Restoring factory defaults
Input Source Select*
Power Control**
 
*: Radio button is on Analog by default (monitor connected via HDMI).
Selecting Digital the first [application start resets said state] time makes the screen go black (an active DP source device is connected). Selecting Digital any other time has no effect.
Selecting Analog sets it into VGA input mode (works flawlessly).
Clicking on the 'Default' button (left facing arrow) will always*** restore HDMI as input source.
 
**: Others -> Power control -> Power control: Set on 'Off' by default. Selecting 'On' turns off the monitor. Selecting 'Off' turns on the monitor.
 
***: Only tested on an HDMI host
 
No (noticeable) effects:
Others -> Degauss -> Secondary Degauss
Others -> OSD -> OSD Orientation Landscape (default) / Portrait
 
System Information:
Ubuntu 18.04.6 LTS (64-bit)
Gnome 3.28.2
Intel x86-64
 
Thank you very much for the display control application! It makes adjusting the screen brightness much faster and more convenient.
 
Regards
Roman Meier
